cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about authorship attribution using neural network language models, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning, specifically deep learning. This suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also discusses the topics of the text samples, which suggests that it could be relevant to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category. Finally, the use of neural networks for language modeling could also place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
